{
  "texts": [
    "Teachers' beliefs and knowledge bases continue to be a focal point, particularly in studies that emphasize the importance of addressing diverse belief systems and knowledge gaps to enhance teaching efficacy.",
    "Finally, the integration of engineering in science education, highlighted in Chinese research, marks a continued evolution in traditional educational frameworks, underscoring the need for comprehensive, interdisciplinary approaches to STEM Collectively, these themes paint a comprehensive picture of the current state and transformative potential of STEM professional development in China.",
    "This study aimed to identify (1) the common objectives and outcomes of STEM PD initiatives in China and how they are reflected in current educational practices and (2) the influence of various PD approaches on STEM teachers' competencies and teaching practices, considering factors such as teacher efficacy and regional differences (see Fig. 11).",
    "STEM pedagogy is highly valued across a multitude of Chinese provinces and districts.",
    "Numerous scholarly inquiries have scrutinized STEM teacher professional development (TPD) longitudinally."
  ]
}